Manual:  K. Engelborghs, T. Luzyanina, G. Samaey. DDE-BIFTOOL v. |version|: 
         a Matlab package for bifurcation analysis of delay differential
         equations. Technical Report TW-330

Note:    Two addenda to this manual are available which describe briefly 
         new functionality  in DDE-BIFTOOL v. 2.03 and |version|.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To install:

* unzipping ddebiftool.zip creates a "dde_biftool" directory (named
  "dde_biftool") containing files: 

  manual.pdf (manual by Engelborghs et al)
  Addendum_Manual_DDE-BIFTOOL_2_03.pdf, ExtensionChanges-v3.pdf
  (addenda, explaining additional functionality)
  
  subfolders:
 
  ddebiftool (basic DDE-BIFTOOL routines),
  demos (example scripts illustrating the use of DDE-BIFTOOL),
  ddebiftool_extra_psol (extension for local bifurcations of periodic orbits),
  ddebiftool_utilities (optional auxiliary functions)
  ddebiftool_extra_rotsym (extension for systems with rotational symmetry).
 
* Testing the tutorial demo neuron:

  run Matlab (version 7.0 or higher) or octave (version 3.2.3 or higher) 
  change working directory inside matlab or octave to demos/neuron
  execute script "rundemo"

* Documentation of demos in html format is accessible from the node
  demos/index.html

Please feel free to mail any feedback concerning the code
(such as the type of application; the problems you encountered; 
or aspects that you would like to see improved). 
Preprints or papers containing results obtained with the package 
are also very welcome.

